  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bramley apples collapse completely during baking, becoming a dense jammy filling rather than discrete slices. That is the right result for a pie filling: it slices cleanly and holds together on the plate. Blackberries add sharp, fruity pockets and keep more of their shape. Do not cook the filling before adding it to the pie; the cornflour thickens the juices as they release in the oven. Cut steam vents in the lid before baking so the steam escapes rather than making the pastry soggy."
          }
        ]
      },
