            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour, sugar, and salt until the mixture resembles rough breadcrumbs with a few larger butter flakes. Add the cold water one tablespoon at a time, mixing until the dough just comes together. Divide two-thirds for the base and one-third for the lid. Flatten each into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assemble and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Roll the larger pastry disc to about 3 mm and use it to line a 23 cm pie dish, pressing into the edges and leaving overhang. Toss the apple slices, blackberries, caster sugar, cornflour, cinnamon, and lemon juice together and pile into the lined dish, mounding slightly in the centre. Roll the remaining pastry to the same thickness and lay over the top. Press the edges together to seal, then trim the overhang and crimp. Cut 4 or 5 steam vents in the lid. Brush with beaten egg. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the pastry is deep golden and the filling is bubbling at the vents. Rest for 15 minutes before serving."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
